    "body": "On master branch, this is now supported using `DialOptions` and the `WithHeader` option. The option works for WebSocket as well.\r\n\r\n```go\r\nmyHeader := rpc.WithHeader(\"x-foo\", \"bar\")\r\nc, err := rpc.DialOptions(context.Background(), \"ws://server\", myHeader)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThere is also a `WithHTTPAuth` option which sets a function that signs the request.\r\nHowever, it will probably not work for AWS authentication. They want a signature over\r\nthe request body, but our `HTTPAuth` function only provides access to the headers.\r\n",
